About the Business

Collov empowers anyone to visualize and create beautiful interiors effortlessly, bridging AI technology with design creativity. With 3M+ registered users, 500+ AI-generated templates, and 50K+ monthly active users, it's one of the leading AI interior design platforms.

The Problem

"1 in every 4 users canceled their subscriptions"

  • Homogenous function compared to competitors
  • Need an approach to ease the design process for pro designers
  • Need a smooth workflow to buy the same furniture in the design

Workflow optimization: Before vs After

Competitive Analysis

Analyzed 4 major competitors: 2020 Design Live, Floorplanner, RoomSketcher, and Kujiale. Each had unique strengths but none offered the complete solution for both professionals and casual users.

Solution: Pro Mode

Designed a dual-mode interface that serves both casual users (simple mode) and professionals (pro mode with floor plan import, 3D space generation, and furniture shopping integration).

Redesigned home page with clear entry points

Style selection & generation

AI Assistant for design help

Key Features Delivered

  • Import Floor Plan / Room Photo — Support CAD files (DWG/DXF) and room photos
  • AI Style Matching — Analyze user preferences with 72% accuracy for style recommendations
  • 3D Space Generation — Generate full 3D renderings from 2D floor plans
  • Shopping Cart Integration — Buy furniture directly from the rendered design
  • AI Assistant — Natural language interface for design modifications

About the Product

Signals Notebook is an AI-powered electronic lab notebook (ELN) trusted by over 10,000 scientific teams worldwide. It connects with ChemDraw, Spotfire, and lab instruments via APIs, supporting over 1M workflows annually.

Key Clients: Pfizer, Roche, Novartis, Johnson & Johnson, Takeda, Moderna, GSK, Merck, AstraZeneca, Bayer, and more.

Key results after 60 days of launch

The Challenge

Scientists needed to track complex biological material lineage (cell lines, proteins, antibodies) but existing solutions like WormWeb, LabKey, and IDBS either lacked scalability, had complex interfaces, or struggled with real-time collaboration.

Recommended Solution

Materials Smart Folder → Select Material → Lineage Tab → View Map & Table → Export Data

Recommended lineage visualization workflow

Materials Smart Folder

Interactive Lineage Map

Key Features

  • Materials Smart Folder — View all types of materials (Cell Lines, Proteins, Antibodies) in one organized view
  • Lineage Map — Interactive visualization showing parent-child relationships with Asset Level (black) and Batch Level (orange) distinction
  • Lineage Table — Tabular view of lineage data with export capability
  • Cross-product Integration — Works seamlessly with Signals Inventa and BioDesign

The Challenge

Building a design system requires navigating multiple stages of difficulty: proposing the initiative to leadership for funding, creating abstract components, getting design teams to adopt new processes, and ensuring continuous contribution back to the system.

Make System → Use System: Navigating the challenges

UX Design Principles

For designing software in the life sciences industry:

Four core principles guiding all design decisions

  • Customers First — We build products that create value for our customers. We partner with them to understand and solve their challenges.
  • Facts Over Opinions — We defer to facts over opinions, using evidence and research-based design philosophy. If you're unsure - ask!
  • Always a Work in Progress — Our focus is on learning, iteration, and continuous improvement. We are agile, always learning, and open to change.
  • Usable by Everyone — We are inherently inclusive and advocate for accessibility in the products we design (WCAG AA compliance).

Design Tokens

AA-compliant color system for Light & Dark modes

Key Deliverables

  • Color System — Primary, Success, Warning, Danger, Neutral colors with AA-compliant contrast ratios
  • Typography — Native Roboto font system with Display, Heading, and Body scales
  • Components — 50+ reusable components in Figma with coded equivalents
  • Documentation — Comprehensive guidelines hosted on revvity.design

About Ctrip

Ctrip is an international OTA (Online Travel Agency) company based in Shanghai, enabling seamless travel experiences for global users. With 400M+ annual active users, 1.5M+ partnered hotels worldwide, and 2M+ verified travel reviews monthly, it's one of the world's largest travel platforms.

Problems Identified

UX issues categorized by type

  • Contents — Video content not cropped properly, black edges appear
  • Sound/Image — No sound on detail page, video playback area too small
  • Operation — Video too long to pause, 5G environment cues unreasonable
  • Bugs — Progress bar not adapted to hotel overview card

Data Analysis

Video and image usage data insights

Key Findings

  • Video Ratio — 70% are 16:9, need optimized cropping for different screen sizes
  • Image Ratio — 47% are 3:2, followed by 4:3 (35%)
  • Video CTR — 4.8% click-through rate vs 2.0% for images
  • Sound Preference — Users prefer sound on (8.4% CTR) vs muted (1.1% CTR)

Solutions Delivered

  • Adaptive Cropping — Smart cropping logic based on screen size (16:9 for large, 2:1 for small)
  • Sound Enhancement — Default sound on with user control, matching user preference data
  • Progress Optimization — Redesigned progress bar that adapts to card sliding
  • Content Guidelines — New standards for hotel video uploads to ensure quality
